@vickdw I was going to ask for your input here, this is my first looking into how expressions have been implemented and I wanted to take a consistent approach before changing anything substantially.
The above is based on the MBDecision.decisionNotEqual() which calls parse.string(json,1) as shown above. If I understand correctly the string method is willing to convert any literals (strings, numbers, booleans) to a string so we end up with a string equality check only. Rather than a numeric != numeric equality check.
Does this match with your understanding?

